				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${I_j} = EM\,{G_j}(T),$$\end{document} where T is the temperature and EM is the emission measure, defined as \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$EM = \int_V {{n^2}} dV,$$\end{document} where n is the particle density, and V the plasma volume. The ratio Rij of the emission in two different filters i, j is then independent of the density, and only a function of the temperature: 3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
